<DOC><DOCNO> AP890623-0169 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-06-23-89 2044EST</FILEID><FIRST>r a BC-APAppointment     06-23 0141</FIRST><SECOND>BC-AP Appointment,0145</SECOND><HEAD>Simon Named Chief of Omaha Bureau</HEAD><DATELINE>OMAHA (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Paul Simon, assistant chief of bureau for TheAssociated Press in Los Angeles, has been named chief of bureau inOmaha.   The appointment was announced Friday by AP President Louis D.Boccardi.   Simon, 37, will direct AP's news and marketing operation inNebraska. He succeeds Dan Day, who recently was named bureau chiefin Seattle.   Simon joined the AP in Los Angeles in 1979 and became news editorin Dallas in 1985. He returned to Los Angeles as assistant bureauchief the following year.   Simon is a native of Yucaipa, Calif. He received an undergraduatedegree for California Polytechnic State University, San Luis Obispo,and a master's from California State University, Northridge.   Prior to joining the AP, Simon worked at the Ventura CountyStar-Free Press in Ventura, Calif.</TEXT></DOC>